The paper focuses on the automatic design of controllers for mobile robots using machine learning techniques, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of fuzzy logic and genetic programming for learning controllers also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of quantified fuzzy rules and multiple granularities for linguistic variables, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The application of the algorithm to real-world environments and the use of obstacle avoidance suggest the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of genetic programming for learning rules is a common technique in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
